title: Yelena Tissina
text:
Yelena Tissina, Rus. Елена Тиссина (born February 10, 1977) is a Russian <a href="canoe%20racing">sprint canoer</a> who competed in the late 1990s and early 2000s. She won two bronze medals at the <a href="ICF%20Canoe%20Sprint%20World%20Championships">ICF Canoe Sprint World Championships</a> with one in <a href="1997%20ICF%20Canoe%20Sprint%20World%20Championships">1997</a> (K-2 200 m) and one in <a href="1998%20ICF%20Canoe%20Sprint%20World%20Championships">1998</a> (K-4 200 m).
Tissina also competed at the <a href="2000%20Summer%20Olympics">2000 Summer Olympics</a> in <a href="Sydney">Sydney</a>, finishing seventh in the <a href="Canoeing%20at%20the%202000%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Women%27s%20K-4%20500%20metres">K-4 500 m</a> event and ninth in the <a href="Canoeing%20at%20the%202000%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Women%27s%20K-2%20500%20metres">K-2 500 m</a> event.
